532365\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 30, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104til1665702908893.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/til1665702908893.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/til1665702908893.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"til1665702908893\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Web Security Threats and Defenses\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Threats to web applications can take many forms, and affect multiple areas of the\n      application. The topics in this section describe those threats in more detail and suggest ways\n      in which you can defend against them. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"til1665702908893__section_w5256ab1b5b1_w5257ab1b5_w5258ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Threats Affecting Application Areas</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Common Threats</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Application Area</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Buffer overflow attacks</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tiy1665702897331.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tiy1665702897331.html\" title=\"In web applications, it is possible for the client to tamper with data, so data from the client should never be trusted. Failure to properly validate input from the client or the environment is a security weakness.\">Data I/O for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xwm1665702708046.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xwm1665702708046.html\" title=\"Auditing access and activity logs on a regular basis helps in detecting attempted or successful intrusions. If there has been unauthorized access of your web application, you need to be able to show the signs of intrusion and prove a user's actions. You should also minimize the information provided in error pages.\">Logging and Auditing Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jkx1665702743178.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jkx1665702743178.html\" title=\"A denial of service attack attempts to make a computer resource unavailable to its intended users.\">Denial of Service Attack</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xwm1665702708046.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xwm1665702708046.html\" title=\"Auditing access and activity logs on a regular basis helps in detecting attempted or successful intrusions. If there has been unauthorized access of your web application, you need to be able to show the signs of intrusion and prove a user's actions. You should also minimize the information provided in error pages.\">Logging and Auditing Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sht1665702669233.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sht1665702669233.html\" title=\"Cross-site scripting vulnerabilities enable an attacker to trick the user’s browser into running code (such as JavaScript, Java, Flash, ActiveX, or VBScript) that is treated as trustworthy, thereby allowing the attacker to obtain a copy of the session ID or inject malicious code into web pages viewed by other users.\">Cross-Site Scripting</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rrs1665702669390.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rrs1665702669390.html\" title=\"Authentication is intended to ensure that users (or computers) accessing the system or application are who they purport to be. Authentication systems range in strength from simple user and password validation to transaction signing.\">Authentication for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oxa1665702908679.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oxa1665702908679.html\" title=\"Web browsers are the clients in a web application, responsible for sending and receiving data to and from the server. The browser interprets and displays HTML, and makes use of interpreters for programming scripts such as JavaScript, PHP, and Flash. It is therefore vulnerable to attacks that intercept and read the data it sends, or cross-site scripting attacks such as site forgery.\">Browser Security</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tiy1665702897331.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tiy1665702897331.html\" title=\"In web applications, it is possible for the client to tamper with data, so data from the client should never be trusted. Failure to properly validate input from the client or the environment is a security weakness.\">Data I/O for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pii1665702668200.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pii1665702668200.html\" title=\"Session management is intended to provide a robust and cryptographically secure association between authenticated users and their sessions. Using session management combined with secure HTTP (HTTPS), you can enforce authorization checks and prevent common attacks such as replay attacks, request forging, and man-in-the-middle attacks.\">Session Management for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pxc1665702669673.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pxc1665702669673.html\" title=\"Data leaks can result from incorrectly specified cookies, unverified client input, and verbose error messages.\">Data Leaks</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xwm1665702708046.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xwm1665702708046.html\" title=\"Auditing access and activity logs on a regular basis helps in detecting attempted or successful intrusions. If there has been unauthorized access of your web application, you need to be able to show the signs of intrusion and prove a user's actions. You should also minimize the information provided in error pages.\">Logging and Auditing Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pxc1665702669673.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pxc1665702669673.html\" title=\"Data leaks can result from incorrectly specified cookies, unverified client input, and verbose error messages.\">Data Leaks</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oxa1665702908679.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oxa1665702908679.html\" title=\"Web browsers are the clients in a web application, responsible for sending and receiving data to and from the server. The browser interprets and displays HTML, and makes use of interpreters for programming scripts such as JavaScript, PHP, and Flash. It is therefore vulnerable to attacks that intercept and read the data it sends, or cross-site scripting attacks such as site forgery.\">Browser Security</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ajn1665702669971.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ajn1665702669971.html\" title=\"Eavesdropping is a web security threat in which intermediate servers or sniffer programs intercept and read HTTP data packets as they traverse intermediate servers en route to their destination.\">Eavesdropping</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oxa1665702908679.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oxa1665702908679.html\" title=\"Web browsers are the clients in a web application, responsible for sending and receiving data to and from the server. The browser interprets and displays HTML, and makes use of interpreters for programming scripts such as JavaScript, PHP, and Flash. It is therefore vulnerable to attacks that intercept and read the data it sends, or cross-site scripting attacks such as site forgery.\">Browser Security</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"key1665702908800.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/key1665702908800.html\" title=\"When you deploy and configure the web application you need to ensure that the application is securely deployed. To do so, the passwords and security mechanisms provided with Uniface must be changed and secured.\">Web Application Configuration and Deployment</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mzh1665702669302.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mzh1665702669302.html\" title=\"Identity spoofing, or IP address spoofing, occurs when an attacker determines the IP address of a network, computer, or network component, and uses it to gain access or submit data under that identity, without being authorized to do so.\">Identity Spoofing</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rrs1665702669390.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rrs1665702669390.html\" title=\"Authentication is intended to ensure that users (or computers) accessing the system or application are who they purport to be. Authentication systems range in strength from simple user and password validation to transaction signing.\">Authentication for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rnq1665702669823.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rnq1665702669823.html\" title=\"Interpreter injection attacks send malicious code that is intended for execution by one of the interpreters that web applications use, both on the server side and in the browser. Common injection attacks include SQL injection, JavaScript injection, HTTP response splitting, and parameter manipulation.\">Interpreter Injection</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tiy1665702897331.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tiy1665702897331.html\" title=\"In web applications, it is possible for the client to tamper with data, so data from the client should never be trusted. Failure to properly validate input from the client or the environment is a security weakness.\">Data I/O for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sit1665702545185.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sit1665702545185.html\" title=\"In a man-in-the-middle (MITM) attack, an attacker intercepts a communication between two machines, and impersonates these machines. Both machines assume they are connected to the other, but they are actually connected to an attacker’s machine, which intercepts all messages, and then steals, monitors, or alters the information in it before sending it on to the machine that it was intended for, if it does so at all.\">Man-In-The-Middle Attacks</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rrs1665702669390.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rrs1665702669390.html\" title=\"Authentication is intended to ensure that users (or computers) accessing the system or application are who they purport to be. Authentication systems range in strength from simple user and password validation to transaction signing.\">Authentication for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"key1665702908800.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/key1665702908800.html\" title=\"When you deploy and configure the web application you need to ensure that the application is securely deployed. To do so, the passwords and security mechanisms provided with Uniface must be changed and secured.\">Web Application Configuration and Deployment</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kcf1665702669602.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kcf1665702669602.html\" title=\"When trying to crack user passwords, attackers can resort to guessing, dictionary attacks, and brute force attacks.\">Password Cracking</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rrs1665702669390.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rrs1665702669390.html\" title=\"Authentication is intended to ensure that users (or computers) accessing the system or application are who they purport to be. Authentication systems range in strength from simple user and password validation to transaction signing.\">Authentication for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"key1665702908800.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/key1665702908800.html\" title=\"When you deploy and configure the web application you need to ensure that the application is securely deployed. To do so, the passwords and security mechanisms provided with Uniface must be changed and secured.\">Web Application Configuration and Deployment</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tcb1665702668270.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tcb1665702668270.html\" title=\"Session fixation is a web security threat in which a user’s session ID is set to one known to an attacker.\">Session Fixation</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rrs1665702669390.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rrs1665702669390.html\" title=\"Authentication is intended to ensure that users (or computers) accessing the system or application are who they purport to be. Authentication systems range in strength from simple user and password validation to transaction signing.\">Authentication for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pii1665702668200.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pii1665702668200.html\" title=\"Session management is intended to provide a robust and cryptographically secure association between authenticated users and their sessions. Using session management combined with secure HTTP (HTTPS), you can enforce authorization checks and prevent common attacks such as replay attacks, request forging, and man-in-the-middle attacks.\">Session Management for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Session replay</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tiy1665702897331.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tiy1665702897331.html\" title=\"In web applications, it is possible for the client to tamper with data, so data from the client should never be trusted. Failure to properly validate input from the client or the environment is a security weakness.\">Data I/O for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"olq1665702669163.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/olq1665702669163.html\" title=\"Session sidejacking is a type of security threat in which an attacker hijacks a session by intercepting and reading network traffic between two parties to steal the session cookie.\">Session Sidejacking</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rrs1665702669390.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rrs1665702669390.html\" title=\"Authentication is intended to ensure that users (or computers) accessing the system or application are who they purport to be. Authentication systems range in strength from simple user and password validation to transaction signing.\">Authentication for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pii1665702668200.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pii1665702668200.html\" title=\"Session management is intended to provide a robust and cryptographically secure association between authenticated users and their sessions. Using session management combined with secure HTTP (HTTPS), you can enforce authorization checks and prevent common attacks such as replay attacks, request forging, and man-in-the-middle attacks.\">Session Management for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"til1665702908893__li_d20813e1_d20814e1_d20815e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Access to confidential data</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"til1665702908893__li_d20816e1_d20817e1_d20818e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Data manipulation</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"til1665702908893__li_d20819e1_d20820e1_d20821e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Execution of unauthorized commands</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"til1665702908893__li_d20822e1_d20823e1_d20824e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Privilege escalation</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"evz1665702908556.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/evz1665702908556.html\" title=\"Authorization ensures that users have appropriate privileges to perform actions or access resources.\">Authorization for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vhb1665702670040.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vhb1665702670040.html\" title=\"Cookies are vulnerable to man-in-the middle attacks if their secure attribute does not match the session connection (HTTP or HTTPS).\">Cookies Containing Sensitive Data</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"til1665702908893__table_d4025e1_d4026e1_d4027e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pii1665702668200.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pii1665702668200.html\" title=\"Session management is intended to provide a robust and cryptographically secure association between authenticated users and their sessions. Using session management combined with secure HTTP (HTTPS), you can enforce authorization checks and prevent common attacks such as replay attacks, request forging, and man-in-the-middle attacks.\">Session Management for Web Applications</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532365\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532365\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Web Security Threats and Defenses Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 30, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Web Security Threats and Defenses Threats to web applications can take many forms, and affect multiple areas of the application. The topics in this section describe those threats in more detail and suggest ways in which you can defend against them. Table 1. Threats Affecting Application Areas Common Threats Application Area Buffer overflow attacks Data I/O for Web Applications Logging and Auditing Web Applications Denial of Service Attack Logging and Auditing Web Applications Cross-Site Scripting Authentication for Web Applications Browser Security Data I/O for Web Applications Session Management for Web Applications Data Leaks Logging and Auditing Web Applications Data Leaks Browser Security Eavesdropping Browser Security Web Application Configuration and Deployment Identity Spoofing Authentication for Web Applications Interpreter Injection Data I/O for Web Applications Man-In-The-Middle Attacks Authentication for Web Applications Web Application Configuration and Deployment Password Cracking Authentication for Web Applications Web Application Configuration and Deployment Session Fixation Authentication for Web Applications Session Management for Web Applications Session replay Data I/O for Web Applications Session Sidejacking Authentication for Web Applications Session Management for Web Applications Access to confidential data Data manipulation Execution of unauthorized commands Privilege escalation Authorization for Web Applications Cookies Containing Sensitive Data Session Management for Web Applications Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}